fileChanges.details:
1. UPDATE the detailsItems selector. Currently:
   const detailsItems = Array.from(panelsContainer.querySelectorAll(':scope > .tabs-item'));
   Change to query wrappers first, then details inside:
   const wrappers = Array.from(panelsContainer.querySelectorAll(':scope > .tabs-item-wrapper'));
   const detailsItems = wrappers.map(w => w.querySelector('.tabs-item'));

2. UPDATE the selectTab() function to set background on wrappers:
   - After opening/closing details elements, add wrapper background logic:
   wrappers.forEach((wrapper, i) => {
     if (i === index) {
       // Check for per-tab color
       const tabColor = wrapper.dataset.tabColor;
       if (tabColor) {
         // Per-tab color is handled by the tabColor class already on details for mobile;
         // for desktop wrapper, we set bg-accent-lighter as default, or the tabColor-specific bg
         wrapper.classList.add('bg-accent-lighter');
       } else {
         wrapper.classList.add('bg-accent-lighter');
       }
     } else {
       wrapper.classList.remove('bg-accent-lighter');
     }
   });

   Actually, looking at the current tabColor implementation more carefully: tabColor is a class name like 'neon-green', 'blue', etc. that gets added to the details element. These likely map to CSS that overrides bg/border colors. For the wrapper approach, the tabColor class should be on the wrapper on desktop (so wrapper gets the colored background), and on details on mobile (for accordion colored state).

   Revised approach for selectTab():
   wrappers.forEach((wrapper, i) => {
     const tabColorClass = wrapper.dataset.tabColor;
     if (i === index) {
       wrapper.classList.add('bg-accent-lighter');
       // If there's a per-tab color, it's already in the class list or needs to be toggled
     } else {
       wrapper.classList.remove('bg-accent-lighter');
     }
   });

3. UPDATE the summary click prevention: the summary is now inside the wrapper > details, but the querySelectorAll for summary still works since we query inside detailsItems. No change needed there since we iterate detailsItems and query summary inside each.

4. UPDATE setMobileMode(): when switching to mobile, remove bg-accent-lighter from all wrappers:
   wrappers.forEach(w => w.classList.remove('bg-accent-lighter'));

5. UPDATE setDesktopMode(): after calling selectTab(), the wrapper backgrounds are set by selectTab() already.

6. The content panel querySelector (.tabs-item-content) still works since it's inside the details element, which is inside the wrapper. No changes needed for ARIA setup.
